    Kanye West has gone on another epic rant.But not on social media; this time the hip-hop star waxed poetic on Ellen DeGeneres' talk show. During an eight-minute-long interview that aired Thursday, West kept it 100, talking about his occasional bizarre antics, including asking Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg for $1 billion on Twitter in February after saying he was $53 million in debt. This led to a GoFundMe campaign that raised some $8,000. West declined the money, which went to Notes for Notes, a nonprofit which builds, equips and staffs after-school recording studios in several major cities. West admitted to DeGeneres that he probably should have asked Zuckerberg for the money on Facebook instead of on a rival social network. "Now I understand why he didn't hit me back...he doesn't use Twitter," he said.








